Wash and dry all produce. Heat the broiler (or grill!) to high or oven to 500 degrees. Soak the @wooden skewers{8} in water, if using. Halve, peel, and finely dice 1 @red onion{1}. Halve, peel, and cut the other @red onion{1} into 1-inch cubes. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in #small pot{} over medium heat. Add 1/2 cup diced onion and @Israeli couscous{1%cup} to the pot. Cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until the onion softens. Add 4 cups water to the pot and bring to a boil. Reduce to a low simmer for ~{15%minutes}, until water is absorbed. Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, finely dice the @Persian cucumber{2}. Core, seed, and finely dice @Roma tomato{2}(diced). Core, seed, and cut the other @Roma tomato{2} into 1-inch cubes. Zest and halve the @lemon{2}. Finely chop the @mint{1/2%ounce}(finely chopped) leaves.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @yogurt{1%unit}, half the lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice, and half the mint. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Israeli Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the cucumber, diced tomato, remaining diced onion, lemon zest, and mint. Stir in a squeeze of lemon and a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

== Shrimp ==

Toss the @shrimp{20%ounce}, cubed onion, and cubed tomato on a #baking sheet{}. Season with the @Southwest spice blend{2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Broil ~{5-6%minutes}, turning once, until lightly charred.

> TIP: You can thread the shrimp and veggies onto skewers and throw them on the grill, too!

== Finish and Plate ==

Stir the Israeli salad into the cooked couscous. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve the shrimp and veggies on a bed of couscous salad and drizzle with yogurt sauce. Enjoy!